missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:7:Its best feature is discipline: it insists on estimate-level gains, it front-loads a Tao screen, and it tries to kill cosmetic rewrites quickly. That is real strength.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:19:### 2. The Tao screen is directionally right but operationally under-specified
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:21:The standard "depends on algebraic structure destroyed by Tao's averaged model" is correct. But the chain uses the weaker proxy "not obviously preserved by Tao's averaged model." That is not enough. Many rewrites can look NS-specific at the identity level and still wash out once one tracks localization, projection, averaging, or frequency interactions.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:38:- positive result: must survive Tao, survive localization, survive robustness, and change closure;
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:45:The mission context already records that the vorticity formulation also hits the same `beta = 4/3` barrier, and that Beltrami cancellation is extremely fragile. That does not make this chain pointless, but it does mean parts of Step 2 and Step 3 are at risk of spending budget re-certifying known negatives rather than testing genuinely live candidates.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:49:### Step 1 - Fix the target interaction and front-load the Tao screen
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:58:- The Tao filter is being applied before the chain has specified how the candidate enters a localized estimate. For many structures, the real question is not whether the bare identity survives averaging, but whether the exact interaction between identity, localization, and projection does.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:81:- The chain waits until after a candidate "appears to improve the estimate" before asking whether the effect is just alignment. That is backwards for this mission. Given what is already known about Beltrami fragility, geometry should be built into the first evaluation, not added as a later purity test.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:84:- The step uses near-Beltrami mainly as a fragility screen. That is fair as a guardrail, but it ignores the possibility that localized high-vorticity regions are exactly where one should expect any non-averaged NS structure to manifest.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:108:- The positive endpoint still uses the standard "why Tao does not immediately erase it" language, which is weaker than what is needed. The chain should require an explicit statement of which feature of the exact NS interaction fails in the averaged model and where that failure enters the estimate.
