missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain is disciplined and worth keeping, but only as a narrowly scoped obstruction branch, not as a broad discovery program for the mission's beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism. Its main strengths are real: it asks for estimate-level gains, it front-loads killing cosmetic rewrites, and it is willing to end negatively. Its main weaknesses are also real: it leaves the target architecture under-specified, states the Tao screen too loosely, treats geometry too much as contamination, and makes the negative endpoint easier to earn than the positive one.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The correct refinement is to fix one inherited estimate architecture at the start, define the gain in one bookkeeping currency, require an explicit Tao discriminator, and treat this branch as a bounded test of whether exact NS reformulations or one tightly specified paired auxiliary quantity can beat the named bottleneck. If not, the obstruction memo is the intended success case.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:19:### 2. The Tao screen is conceptually right but operationally too weak
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:23:This is a central flaw. "Not obviously preserved by Tao's averaged model" is too loose. The refined chain needs a concrete statement of what exact NS feature is supposed to fail in the averaged setting and where that failure enters the localized estimate.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:47:This concern is real but not fatal. The project already knows that the vorticity route hits the same `beta = 4/3` barrier and that Beltrami cancellation is fragile. Retesting those directions is only justified if the refined chain states exactly what new localized estimate, commutator accounting, or Tao-relevant comparison is being added.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:75:This is a fair criticism. Given what is already known about Beltrami fragility, geometry should be part of the first serious evaluation, not a late purity test. The refined chain should specify the perturbation metric early and classify candidate signals as generic, geometry-entangled, or geometry-only.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:94:4. Replace the loose Tao filter with an explicit NS-versus-averaged discriminator.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:104:Most of that probability lies on a useful negative result: a disciplined memo showing that, within one fixed estimate architecture and a tightly defined candidate family, exact NS reformulations do not produce a Tao-relevant gain except possibly through geometry-dominated or architecture-changing effects. The chance of a genuinely positive lead remains materially lower, but not zero once the chain allows one tightly controlled auxiliary-quantity route.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:13:The attack is right that the Tao/NS-specificity filter is not operational enough as written. "Identify the exact ingredient" is still too impressionistic unless each candidate ingredient is translated into a concrete benchmark against averaged-model robustness and against known geometric regularity mechanisms. The critique is also right that transport laws, algebraic identities, and multiscale coherence mechanisms should not be mixed without separate tests.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:25:The attacker is right that "Beltrami deficit," "vorticity-direction regularity," and "tube persistence" are not cleanly disjoint until localization scales, amplitude thresholds, and scenario classes are fixed. The refined chain should define observables jointly with the localization protocol rather than pretending they are independent primitives.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:33:### 5. Step 2 is too anchored to known criteria and to "Beltrami deficit alone"
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:37:This is a real weakness. The original chain would too quickly conclude failure if Beltrami deficit alone does not imply an existing criterion. A viable route may require a hybrid observable, for example Beltrami deficit plus concentration, anisotropy, or tube-family coherence. The refined chain should allow that.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:85:This is a real issue. Because the chain sits directly in an area with substantial prior work, it needs explicit calibration against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda, later vorticity-direction coherence work, and related geometric depletion or near-Beltrami discussions before claiming novelty or NS-specificity.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:100:- calibrate against prior art before invoking novelty or Tao-blocking;
