The local repository does have relevant material. The strongest usable sources are the far-field pressure obstruction notes, the meta screening rules, and the run-002 geometry planning docs. The geometry benchmark itself is mostly encoded in mission artifacts rather than in standalone factual-library entries.

**1. Geometry benchmark**
- The step-002 goal explicitly asks for a benchmark of direction coherence, geometric depletion, and near-Beltrami/alignment routes before any observable design. See [step-002 goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-002/GOAL.md:15) and [required deliverables](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-002/GOAL.md:29).
- The best geometry-specific local materials are [run-002 refined chain 02](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/refined/chain-02.md:26), [run-002 selected chain 02](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/selected/chain-02.md:5), [run-002 refined chain 03](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/refined/chain-03.md:30), and [run-002 selected chain 03](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/selected/chain-03.md:23).
- Those docs consistently separate three candidate ideas: local Beltrami alignment, vorticity-direction coherence, and tube persistence. They treat these as distinct and warn that they are not interchangeable mechanisms.
- The overlap boundary is explicit: if a candidate is only static Calderon-Zygmund geometry, or only a restatement of known geometric regularity, it is not live enough for Step 2. See [run-002 refined chain 02](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/refined/chain-02.md:29) and [step-002 goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-002/GOAL.md:50).

**2. Claim boundaries**
- The far-field pressure library is the sharpest local boundary on what counts as real progress versus relabeling. It pins down the live pairing `I_p^far`, the dominant `grad phi_k` term, the constant-mode kill, the surviving affine-and-higher moments, and the fixed-energy coefficient obstruction. See [far-field index](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/INDEX.md:8), [exact pairing](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/exact-surviving-far-field-pairing.md:7), [constant mode killed](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/constant-harmonic-mode-is-automatically-killed.md:9), [affine and higher survive](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/affine-and-higher-harmonic-modes-survive-as-moments.md:5), and [bad coefficient](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/bad-coefficient-stays-at-fixed-energy-scale.md:5).
