+# Exploration 002 Goal — Tao-Screen Table for Geometry Ingredients
+
+## Objective
+
+Operationalize the Tao screen for the geometry route in a way later steps can apply mechanically.
+
+Classify the route's candidate ingredients into the chain's three buckets:
+
+- transport or propagation structure
+- exact algebraic structure
+- multiscale coherence or concentration structure
+
+For each bucket and for each concrete candidate family named locally
+
+- local Beltrami deficit or alignment
+- vorticity-direction coherence
+- tube coherence or persistence
+- hybrid geometric candidates explicitly suggested by the local chain materials
+
+state:
+
+- what Tao-style averaged or toy models plausibly preserve
+- what they plausibly destroy
+- what estimate-level target the ingredient would need to move
+- and whether the candidate is `live`, `weak but informative`, or `collapsed to Tao-robust/static geometry`
+
+## Success Criteria
+
+- Produces a usable Tao-screen table, not just prose.
+- Distinguishes static singular-integral geometry from genuinely NS-specific transport/stretching/coherence dynamics.
+- Reuses the step-001 lesson mechanically:
+  ask what estimate changes and what term becomes smaller.
+- Gives a short reason for every verdict.
+- Ends with a clear recommendation on whether Step 2 should proceed and, if so, which ingredients survive.
+
+## Failure Criteria
+
+- Keeps a candidate alive without naming a target interaction or controlled term.
+- Treats "looks NS-specific" as sufficient without saying what Tao-style averaging destroys.
+- Collapses transport, algebraic, and coherence claims into one undifferentiated geometry label.
+- Ignores the chain's requirement that the eventual target is the full stretching mechanism `S omega . omega`.
+
+## Required Source Anchors
+
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-002/GOAL.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/MISSION.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/refined/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/selected/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/generic-harmonic-regularity-fails-the-tao-gate.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/meta/obstruction-screening/demand-estimate-level-action-on-the-live-obstruction.md`
+
+## Constraints
+
+- Use local repository materials only.
+- Be explicit about which parts of the Tao screen are `[VERIFIED]` from local texts and which are `[INFERRED]` extensions to the geometry route.
+- Do not move into final observable design, localization protocol, or kernel-level decomposition.
+- Do not count local control of `u x omega` or another local fragment as if it were already control of full stretching.
+
+## Deliverables
+
+Write:
+
+1. `REPORT.md` with the Tao-screen table and reasoning.
+2. `REPORT-SUMMARY.md` with:
+   - goal
+   - what was tested
+   - outcome
+   - one key takeaway
+   - the bucket-by-bucket verdicts
+   - whether a synthesis exploration is justified
