+# Exploration 001 Goal — Prior-Art Benchmark for the Geometry Route
+
+## Objective
+
+Benchmark the geometry-route candidate families against the prior-art geometry frameworks explicitly named in the local repository context, and state where this branch would merely restate that literature rather than add a mission-live ingredient.
+
+Use the local corpus to calibrate three candidate families:
+
+- vorticity-direction coherence / direction-regularity routes
+- geometric depletion / local Beltrami or alignment routes
+- tube coherence or persistence routes
+
+The benchmark must answer, for each family:
+
+- what framework the local corpus says already exists
+- what estimate-level or claim-level boundary that framework earns
+- what overlap would make a new claim only a relabeling
+- what gap remains before the chain could honestly call the ingredient live
+
+## Success Criteria
+
+- Produce a source-based benchmark memo, not a generic survey.
+- Separate `[VERIFIED]` repository-supported claims from `[INFERRED]` calibration judgments.
+- Name exact source files for every major benchmark claim.
+- State at least one explicit "forbid novelty claim" rule for each candidate family.
+- End with a bounded verdict on whether the branch still has any ingredients worth carrying into Step 2.
+
+## Failure Criteria
+
+- Treats planning rhetoric as if it were already a theorem claim.
+- Calls a route novel without stating what prior-art framework it overlaps.
+- Uses descriptive vortex language without tying it to a concrete claim boundary.
+- Ignores the pressure-side obstruction memo as the main negative reference point for static singular-integral geometry.
+
+## Required Source Anchors
+
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-002/GOAL.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/MISSION.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/refined/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/selected/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/factual/far-field-pressure-obstruction/INDEX.md`
+
+## Constraints
+
+- Use local repository materials only.
+- Do not pretend the repository contains full prior-art papers if it only contains mission summaries or planning notes.
+- Be explicit when the benchmark is inferred from the mission's local record rather than directly reconstructed from external literature.
+- Forbid novelty claims that amount only to static Calderon-Zygmund, singular-integral, or alignment-language restatements.
+- Keep the output tied to the three candidate families above; do not broaden the candidate list.
+
+## Deliverables
+
+Write:
+
+1. `REPORT.md` with the benchmark memo and claim-boundary analysis.
+2. `REPORT-SUMMARY.md` with:
+   - goal
+   - what was checked
+   - outcome
+   - one key takeaway
+   - the benchmark verdict for each candidate family
+   - whether any family remains live enough to justify Step 2 work
