+## Constraints
+
+- Use local repository materials only.
+- Do not pretend the repository contains full prior-art papers if it only contains mission summaries or planning notes.
+- Be explicit when the benchmark is inferred from the mission's local record rather than directly reconstructed from external literature.
+- Forbid novelty claims that amount only to static Calderon-Zygmund, singular-integral, or alignment-language restatements.
+- Keep the output tied to the three candidate families above; do not broaden the candidate list.
+
+## Deliverables
